problem_statement:
`LogConsolePanel › #source › displays output only from the current source` test is failing on CI
Seen in a couple of PRs now and on main:

```js
 FAIL  test/widget.spec.ts (14.931 s)
  ● LogConsolePanel › #source › displays output only from the current source

    expect(received).not.toBeNull()

    Received: null

      101 |       const nodeA = logConsole.node.querySelector('#A')!;
      102 |       const nodeB = logConsole.node.querySelector('#B')!;
    > 103 |       expect(nodeA).not.toBeNull();
          |                         ^
      104 |       expect(anyAncestor(nodeA, isHiddenLumino)).toBe(false);
      105 |       expect(nodeB).not.toBeNull();
      106 |       expect(anyAncestor(nodeB, isHiddenLumino)).toBe(true);

      at Object.<anonymous> (test/widget.spec.ts:103:25)


Error: expect(received).not.toBeNull()

Received: null

    at Object.<anonymous> (test/widget.spec.ts:103:25)
```

This is because we no longer allow identifier in the sanitizer by default. The test should be rewritten to use a different selector, like a class name.

